<br>
A chorus of voices speak up in understanding, and she curtsies, silently bidding them goodnight. As she walks back to the druid guild where she will be spending the night, she feels the little hairs on the back of her neck stand up as she senses eyes upon her. She looks back to the fire, but the party's eyes are locked on a grizzled old shaman animatedly telling his tale. Shrugging to herself, Isharra continues toward the guild, not giving the feeling a second thought. It was not an unpleasant feeling, anyway. <p><i>Isharra Moonsong</i><BR>
