Note: This is Isharra's private journal entry, so what you read here is not something your character would know in game. This is to add more depth to my character because she tends to be very aloof and emotionally distant from others, so it is hard for people to see what she really feels and thinks. So, please keep in mind that what you read here should not be repeated as in-character knowledge. If she writes that Sinadwen is her secret love (haha, not likely! just an example), none would have any way of knowing that, short of finding her journal, which she keeps well hidden in her cleavage! So back off, buddy! /ooc off </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
Hello, little book. <br>
<br>
How strange it feels writing to you, but I need something to help me sort out my thoughts. The raid into Lower Guk hunt went well last night, except for the minor issue of our complete and total annihilation by the Lord and his knights late in the evening. Praise the gods that they saw fit to allow our spirits to return to our bodies, and praise Tunare for my gift of resurrection that helped complete the process of reanimation. I still wish to get a braided cinch cord for Deneteth, which I hear a Frogluk sage carries on him, as well as the arch magus's robes. My dear wizard friend deserves them for all his dedication to the Band. <br>
<br>
Gatsu is quite an able warrior, and after having only ventured in Lower Guk once before with us, he already seems to know the place well. That was a pleasant surprise, and he is very efficient at what he does. I also got to meet a Druidess by the name of Bryer, who joined us in our exploits later in the evening. From watching her and Gatsu, I think there is more than just friendship to their relationship, but I've never been the best at determining such things, and they could just be very close companions. Perhaps I'm just looking to see something where nothing is, as if I'm trying to make my own dull life a bit more romantic, vicariously through them. <br>
<br>
Sinadwen showed a thoughtful side I am not accustomed to tonight. Even though he was wrong in his summation that I'm &quot;chilly,&quot; it was interesting to hear him address a topic seriously, without mocking me. He asked me why that, since I have already fled from my obligation to marry Gareth, I still insist on honoring the betrothal by my chastity. Why do I? I answered that it is a warped sense of honor to my father, and I suppose that's the case, though Sinadwen reads more into it. Bah. <br>
<br>
Well, my eyes are starting to droop. I'd best sleep. Runnyeye is tomorrow, and I want to be alert. Thanks for listening, little book. Goodnight.<br>
 <p><i>Isharra Moonsong</i><BR>
<i>Priestess of Tunare</i><br>
