<br>
I sat thinking tonight about the dark elf I met in Greater Faydark the night Anders and I visited Mistmoore. What makes a person good? Gatsu has surely shown his value in his efforts to aid the band, even though he was once a slave to hate. What of Cronadan? I was taught that all Teir'Dal are to be hated and that they are too far gone from the light to ever be redeemed. Yet, they are also children of the Mother, children stolen from her womb and mistreated until they became monsters. Can that shred of Koada'dal in them be reached? Certainly Cronadan has gone out of his way to distance himself from the sins of his people and has even found acceptance among most of the goodly folks of the land, including the Fier'Dal. Mayhaps he is evidence of some hope for peace one day? <br>
<br>
But for now, I cannot dwell on fantasies. The reality is that the Teir'Dal are bent upon our destruction. So I will continue to contemplate Cronadan, but my purpose as it concerns the rest of the Teir'Dal is clear: destroy or be destroyed. <p><i>Isharra Moonsong</i><BR>
<i>Priestess of Tunare</i><br>
